Cape Town â€“ The police are investigating a case of murder after a second body was found on Table Mountain this week. The body of a man was discovered on Chapman's Peak at 11am on Wednesday morning. "Circumstances surrounding the body of a man who was found at about 11:00 (Wednesday) by one of the park's cleaners on Chapmans Peak are under investigation," police spokesperson FC van Wyk said. "He was found with his hands tied and was naked and had visible injuries. A murder case was opened for investigation. Investigation continues. Anyone with any information about this fatal incident is kindly requested to contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111 or Hout Bay SAPS." On Tuesday, the body of a woman was discovered on Platteklip Gorge. The investigation into her death continues.  marvin.charles@inl.co.za  Cape Argus